news.title: WNS Global sells 1.7 lakh sq ft office in Pune, leases it back for five years
news.para: The company has sold the office spanning across five floors in Magarpatta Cybercity in Hadapsar locality for Rs 177 crore and leased it back at annual rentals of Rs 16 crore, allowing it to retain its existing workspace.

news.title: Interarch Building Products' profit rises 28% to Rs 28 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 369.27 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year from Rs 321.24 crore in the year-ago period, according to a regulatory filing on Tuesday.

news.title: Ambuja Neotia Group to invest over Rs 15,000 crore in West Bengal in next five years
news.para: Ambuja Neotia Group aims to deliver 10.5 million sq ft of built space across residential and commercial sectors over the next four to five years. It will be investing Rs 6,500 crore across nine real estate projects.

news.title: MHADA to construct eight lakh houses in five years: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: Shinde, minister for Housing & Urban Development, made the announcement at a lottery for 2,147 houses and 117 plots in the Konkan division.

news.title: Sunny Leone buys office space in Mumbai for Rs 8 crore
news.para: Sunny Leone purchased the office space from Aishwarya Property and Estates, owned by Anand Kamalnayan Pandit and Roopa Anand Pandit.

news.title: Pune: Kharadi residents to receive property cards by April-end
news.para: Diwase said the two-day enquiry required for digitisation was scheduled for Feb 6 and 7, and would involve 60 officials from Pune, Satara, Sangli, Solapur and Kolhapur districts to carry out door-to-door visits.

news.title: Bhutani Infra discontinues talks with WTCA
news.para: Bhutani Infra had acquired a majority stake in WTC Noida in a revenue-share deal. This was one of five World Trade Centers being developed in India. The company clarified that they have withdrawn from this agreement.

news.title: Ranchi civic body issues eviction notices to 232 flats' occupants
news.para: Out of 336 flats in Madhukam, 140 are reportedly occupied without documentation. Out of 352 flats in Rugdigarha, 92 were taken over.

news.title: Centre denies ownership rights to Chandigarh rehabilitation colony allottees
news.para: Union minister of state, home affairs, Nityanand Rai said, "These houses were allotted to economically weaker sections of society on a monthly licence fee basis or leasehold basis. In these rehabilitation schemes, there is no provision to get ownership rights."

news.title: Punjab chief information commissioner orders survey of illegal colonies in Ludhiana
news.para: The directions — aimed at preventing further financial losses to the state exchequer — come while disposing of a case filed by a Ludhiana resident.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh cabinet allocates Rs 50,000 crore for housing projects for urban poor
news.para: ​Under the Awas Yojana, 10 lakh houses will be constructed in five years to benefit the eligible beneficiary families of economically weaker, lower-and middle-income groups in the urban areas.

news.title: Zomato looking to lease up to two million sq ft in Gurugram
news.para: Zomato, which currently occupies more than 300,000 sq ft of office space developed by ASF and the Pioneer Group in Gurugram, is in talks with the same developers for built-to-suit assets.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh's planning department to soon conduct quarterly audits of EPC projects
news.para: Independent auditors and civil engineers with expertise in examining the structural durability of raw materials and the structure of a building will be deputed to evaluate the quality of a project.

news.title: Hyderabad: HYDRAA conducts two demolition drives in Shamshabad
news.para: One key complaint involved a 998-square-yard public park in Southern Paradise (Sri Sampath Nagar), which was allegedly seized by private parties.

news.title: Over 30 illegal colonies razed, 172 FIRs lodged in Ghaziabad in one year
news.para: "Between Jan 1, 2024, and Jan 17, 2025, GDA carried out anti-encroachment demolition drives across all its eight zones. A total of 87 illegal structures and hutments were razed and over 60,000 sqm of land was reclaimed from land grabbers and secured," a GDA official said.

news.title: Hyderabad: Property worth Rs 150 crore in Jubilee Hills seized in benami transactions case
news.para: The property was registered in Rathi's name in 2017 through two sale deeds of ₹4 crore each, bringing the total sale consideration to ₹8 crore. However, the BPU has estimated the property's current market value to be ₹150 crore.

news.title: Noida: Over 300 employees of Supertech protest over unpaid salary
news.para: Both groups have recently approached the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT), seeking its intervention and an order to interim resolution professional (IRP) Hitesh Goel to clear the dues.

news.title: Greater Noida development body may extend penalty waiver for delays in flats' registries
news.para: Introduced in July 2024 for a six-month period, the waiver has already benefited over 6,500 homebuyers, each receiving a waiver of penalties ranging from Rs 2 lakh to Rs 2.5 lakh.

news.title: Builders can't deduct over 10% of base price in case of cancellation by homebuyers: SC
news.para: A bench of Justices B R Gavai and S V N Bhatt said the contractual terms which are ex facie one-sided, unfair and unreasonable would constitute unfair trade practice.

news.title: Insolvency board issues discussion paper to streamline corporate resolution process
news.para: The paper proposes several amendments to address operational challenges in the resolution framework. The IBBI has invited public comments on the discussion paper till February 25 through its website.
